   General Federal Information Sites

   The Resource Directory for Older People
   Intended to serve a wide audience, this directory from the
   Administration on Aging contains names, addresses, phone numbers, and
   fax numbers of organizations which provide information and other
   resources on matters relating to the needs of older persons.

   Membership Organizations for Seniors
   Membership organizations listed on this Administration on Aging web
   site reflect the diversity of backgrounds and interests of older
   individuals. While they share some common interests, they also reflect
   different political, ideological, economic and social viewpoints.

   U.S. Government Blue Pages Online Directory:

   A project that reinvents the way that Federal, State, County, Local,
   and Tribal government services are listed in 6,000 telephone
   directories distributed to over 91 million households.

   The Catalog of Federal Domestic Assistance Programs
   The Catalog of Federal Domestic Assistance Programs (CFDA) is a
   government-wide compendium of all 1,458 Federal programs, projects,
   services, and activities that provide assistance or benefits to the
   American public. These programs provide grants, loans, loan guarantees,
   services, information, scholarships, training, insurance, etc., to
   millions of Americans every day.

   General Non-Profit Information Sites

   American Association of Retired Persons:

   AARP 55 ALIVE Mature Driving Program:
   AARP 55 ALIVE/Mature Driving is the nation's first and largest
   classroom driver improvement course specially designed for motorists
   age 50 and older.   It is intended to help older drivers improve their
   skills while teaching them to avoid accidents and traffic violations.

   AARP Site For Grandparents
   Find the latest facts about grandparent-headed households and where to
   turn for help and support.


